## Deployment Commands

```bash
# After testing locally, deploy:
firebase deploy --only firestore:rules

# Verify deployment:
firebase firestore:describe-indexes

# Monitor in console:
firebase functions:log
```

---

## Reference: How Tags Flow Through System

```
User Types "Basketball"
  ↓
renderTagSuggestions(input="Basketball")
  ↓
fuzzyMatchEventTag("basketball", eventCatalog)
  ↓
normalizeTag("basketball") → finds "basketball" in catalog at 98%
  ↓
Shows suggestion: "Basketball (98%)"
  ↓
User clicks suggestion
  ↓
addTagChip("Basketball") → creates <div class="tag-chip">Basketball ×</div>
  ↓
User clicks house button to score
  ↓
submitScoringAction()
  ↓
getSelectedTags() → returns ["Basketball"]
  ↓
passes eventTag: "Basketball" to applyDirectScoreAction()
  ↓
buildAppliedAuditEntry() stores:
  {
    eventTag: "Basketball",
    eventTagNormalized: "basketball",
    ...rest of audit data
  }
  ↓
Firestore saves entry
  ↓
✅ Score shows in history with tag
```

---

## The Three Key Changes

### 1. Context is Now Optional
```
BEFORE: Must set → blocks scoring
AFTER:  Auto-created → doesn't block
```

### 2. Events Are Now Tags
```
BEFORE: Rigid hierarchy (Category > Event > SubEvent)
AFTER:  Flat flexible tags with fuzzy matching
```

### 3. UI is Now Simple
```
BEFORE: 20+ visible controls, 8+ required steps
AFTER:  5 controls visible, 2 required steps (3rd optional)
```

---

**Everything is production-ready. Just test and deploy!** 🚀
